  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C).",
    "Cut chicken into small pieces and season with salt and pepper. Roast in the preheated oven for about 15 minutes until golden brown.",
    "In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic, sauté for 3-4 minutes or until translucent.",
    "Add minced ginger to the skillet, stirring well for an additional minute. Mix in roasted chicken pieces.",
    "Stir in soy sauce, hoisin sauce, lemon juice, and chicken stock cube. Bring to a simmer, then let it thicken slightly by reducing the heat.",
    "Incorporate sesame seeds into the sauce just before serving for added texture and flavor."
